# Overview

This report applies a probabilistic modeling framework to predict every game of the NCAA Tournament. Win probabilities are estimated using a logistic function applied to adjusted efficiency margins (AdjEM = AdjO − AdjDef). The tournament is then simulated 100,000 times via Monte Carlo methods to estimate each team's probability of advancing through every round.

