# Probabilistic Model

Win probability follows a logistic function on the efficiency margin difference:

$$P(\text{win}) = \frac{1}{1 + \exp(-(E_1 - E_2) / \sigma)}$$

where $\sigma$ is a scaling parameter calibrated to historical NCAA tournament data. We use $\sigma = 10$, which is consistent with published estimates from KenPom-based models.

```{r win-prob-function}
sigma <- 10

win_prob <- function(em1, em2, sigma = 10) {
  1 / (1 + exp(-(em1 - em2) / sigma))
}
```

